---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy · a → b">
  <h1 class="mb-6 text-3xl font-bold">Privacy</h1>

  <p class="mb-8 text-xl font-medium">Your files never leave your device.</p>

  <div class="space-y-6 text-base leading-relaxed">
    <p>
      This is not a marketing claim — it's an architectural fact. There is no upload endpoint on
      this site. All conversion happens in your browser using WebAssembly.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold">What we don't do</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
      <li>We don't upload your files anywhere.</li>
      <li>We don't use Google Analytics, Meta Pixel, or any third-party tracker.</li>
      <li>We don't set tracking cookies.</li>
      <li>We don't load fonts, scripts, or images from third parties.</li>
      <li>We don't show ads.</li>
      <li>We don't have user accounts.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold">Verify it yourself</h2>
    <ol class="list-decimal space-y-2 pl-6">
      <li>Open your browser's DevTools and select the Network tab.</li>
      <li>Drop in a file and convert it.</li>
      <li>You'll see zero outbound requests during conversion.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold">What we do store, locally</h2>
    <p>
      We use your browser's <code class="rounded bg-black/5 px-1 dark:bg-white/10">localStorage</code>
      to remember your theme preference (light/dark) and last-used output format. That data never
      leaves your device. You can clear it anytime via your browser's site settings.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold">If we ever break this</h2>
    <p>
      Please open an issue on
      <a
        href="https://github.com/rosscyking1115/a-to-b"
        class="underline hover:no-underline"
        rel="noopener">GitHub</a
      >. The privacy promise is non-negotiable; any change that adds a tracker, third-party request,
      or upload endpoint would be a bug.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
